  "text": "In the phylogenetic tree of VP7 nucleotide sequences showed in Fig. 3a , the G1P [CITATION_1] RV strains from Caracas (2007) (2008) were grouped in a unique branch, revealing more than 99.8% identities to each other at nucleotide level, and 100% at amino acid level (data not shown). These strains were clustered into the lineage I together with G1 reference strains from India reported in the years 2002, 2007 and 2008 (respectively ISO-4, NIV-0716581 and NIV-088325), for which showed the highest (≥99.5%) nucleotide identities.",
